		<tr align="left" valign="top">
			<td class="BoardRowA">
			<a class="AuthorLink" href="/user.asp?usr=8839">Gale^of^Northwind</a>&nbsp;<img src=/images/star.gif border=0 hspace=0 vspace=0 alt="87 posts">&nbsp;			
			</td>
			<td class="BoardRowA">5/10 7:38pm</td>
			<td class="BoardRowA"><a name="5613249"><span style="font-weight: bold;">
				On RP'ing (and a quick note to Lothanon and Co.)
			</span></a></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				There seems to have been a lot of talk lately about the nature of RP'ing and its comodity in Everquest; the conditions it survives under, the game's problems, etc.  I agree that on PvP servers the race to race fighting makes for a better atmosphere in a military respect, but what about KS'ers and the fact that the races kill their own kinds or those people with the same alignments?  That's not really RP'ing either if all you're after is the loot.  I know this will generate another heated debate, and I welcome it, as I've seen very well-reasoned and insightful people here (mostly). <br>  <br> Nonetheless, on the blue servers (and red, to an extent), it seems now imperitive that player driven quests which are complicated enough to act as loose plots be engeniered if the bloody GM's and Verant won't do anything.  To aid in the spread of ideas for types of quests and the various scenarios wich we could come up with, I propose that a forum or e-mail ring be set up to facilitate discussion by people who want to start PDQ's.  I personally do not have the computer expertise to do this at the moment, I merely wish to hear everyone's thoughts on the idea.  Thank you. <br>  <br> And to Lothanon and Co., I will still be around, I merely wanted to &quot;step out for a moment&quot;.  RL is too much, but I'll be back in a few weeks, and check the board weekly. <br>  <br> -Gale of Northwind		

